race.comment: Lots of these look to be making up the numbers. NORTHERN CHILD (7) is a four start maiden who has placed twice. Placed at the mile two back then dropped back to 1400m latest and was a solid fifth. Has drawn an outside gate the last three starts and finally draws well. Gets chance to get off the mark. ALPINE HONEY (1) rolled forward two back and placed then was snagged back last time and didn't come on. Tricky gate but has naturally good early speed and expected to give a sight. WHITE STAR SUZIE (10)made debut over 1400m and ran very well, coming from near last to place. Has good upside and suited by the extra ground. SAVAGE RIVER (8)  has raced three times and placed last two. Looks close to a win and senior rider sticks. Looks one of the hardest to beat with any improvement. DA SILVER FLASH (11) is mixing form but fitter and may well be looking for the mile now.
